      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:40:3",
      "text": [
        " قُلْتُ رَجُلٌ قَطَعَ رَأْسَ مَيِّتٍ فَقَالَ حُرْمَةُ الْمَيِّتِ كَحُرْمَةِ الْحَيِّ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad, from Muhammad Bin Sinan, from the one who informed him, ",
          "Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘I said, ‘A man cuts-off the head of a deceased’. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘The sanctity of the dead is like the sanctity of the living’."
        ]
      }
